## 2026-03-28 - `weightToFontStyle` mapping in controller uses hardcoded English style names — fonts using "Book", "Roman", "Demi" etc. cause `loadFontAsync` to throw, silently skipping typography application
- Replaced `weightToFontStyle` (hardcoded weight→style mapping) with `resolveStyleForWeight`, which queries `figma.listAvailableFontsAsync()` for the actual font family's available styles, maps each to a numeric weight via `fontStyleToWeight`, and picks the closest match. Falls back to the original hardcoded mapping if the API call fails or the font isn't installed. Also expanded `fontStyleToWeight` to recognize "Book", "Roman", "Normal", "Demi" as alternate style names.
- Files changed: `packages/figma-plugin/src/plugin/controller.ts` ~L1392 (fontStyleToWeight expansion), ~L1405 (new resolveStyleForWeight), ~L335 and ~L839 (call sites)
- **Learnings for future iterations:**

